            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition">
                        <div type="textpart">
                            <ab>(S) Dum in Dei nomine, in <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/83">Florentino</geogName>, prope
                            <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers">Arni</placeName>, in loco qui nominatur <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Mention #Residential #Itinerary"
                            ref="#places/533">Omiclo</placeName> in iudicio residebat domnus
                            <persName key="#Chancellor #Missus_regis"><name ref="Guntherius"
                                >Gunterius</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancelarius</rs> et <rs key="#Missus_regis"
                            >missus</rs> domni inperatoris iusticias faciendas ac delibearandas,
                        adesent cum eo <persName key="#Judge"><name ref="Bonusfilius"
                                >Bonusfilius</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge"><name
                                ref="Otto">Otto</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Judge #Missus_regis"><name ref="Atto">Atto</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Judge"><name ref="Wibertus">Wiberto</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Judge"><name ref="Burgundius"
                            >Burgundius</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge"><name
                                ref="Wolcausus">Wolcausus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge"
                                ><name ref="Tolbertus">Tolbertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudices</rs> sacri palacii et reliqui plures. Ibique eorum
                        veniens presencie <persName key="#Advocatus"><name ref="Lanfrancus"
                                >Lanfrancus</name></persName>, <rs key="#Advocatus">avocatus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monesterii</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/126">Sancti
                            Bartholomei</orgName>, sito loco qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/281">Curtis Mainberti</placeName>, et
                        cepit dicere: “Iam plures vice me reclamavi ad vos, donnus Gunterius
                        cancelarius et missus, super <persName><name ref="Bonifacius"
                                >Bonefacium</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Ebbo"
                                >Eponem</name></persName> et supra <persName><name ref="Rainerius"
                                >Ranerium</name></persName> filium <persName><name ref="Willa"
                                >Wille</name></persName> qui parti predicti monesterii malo ordine
                        et contra legem detinent <foreign><rs key="#Landed_possessions">omne quod
                                abemus</rs> in <placeName key="#Landed_possessions"
                                ref="#places/348">Alma</placeName></foreign> et contradicent
                        nominative medietatem de <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> una que noncupatur
                            <geogName key="#Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Churches"
                            ref="#estates/235"><placeName ref="#places/281" key="#Curtes #Churches"
                                >Sesstinga</placeName></geogName> cum <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casis</rs> et <rs key="#Churches"
                            >capellis</rs> seu teritoriis omnibusque rebus que ad ipsam medietatem
                        de iamdicta corte et capella pertinente; nam aliam medietatem de iamdicta
                        corte et capella sive rebus omnibus ad parte suprascripto monesterii a
                        proprietatem pertinet;. Et sive medietate de <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs>
                        una qui noncupatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Churches" ref="#estates/236"
                                ><placeName key="#Curtes" ref="#places/534"
                            >Columnata</placeName></geogName> cum <rs key="#Churches">ecclexiis</rs>
                        casis teritoriis et omnibus rebus que ad ipsa medietas de predicta curte et
                        ecclesiis pertinet; reliquam namque medietas pars ipsius monesterii a
                        proprietatem ipsius monesterii detinent. Et sive medietatem de <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curte</rs> que noncupatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Castle #Tower #Churches"
                            ref="#estates/239"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Castle #Tower #Churches"
                                ref="#places/282">Valle</placeName></geogName>, cum <rs key="#Tower"
                            >turre</rs> et <rs key="#Castle">castello</rs> et <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesia</rs> ibi consistente, et cum <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casis</rs> territoriis et omnibus rebus
                        que ad ipsam medietatem de iam dicto castello et turre et curte pertinent;
                        aliam namque medietatem ipsius curtis ad proprietam ipse monasterium
                        detinet. Et sive medietatem de <rs key="#Curtes">corte</rs>, que nominatur
                            <geogName
                            key="#Lakes #Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fisheries #Pigs #Ports #Churches"
                            ref="#estates/240"><placeName
                                key="#Lakes #Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fisheries #Pigs #Ports #Churches"
                                ref="#places/313">Portilione</placeName></geogName>, cum <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casis</rs>, <rs key="#Churches"
                            >capellis</rs> seu territoriis, et <rs key="#Lakes">lacu</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Fisheries #Fish">piscaria</rs> et <rs key="#Ports">portu</rs>,
                        omnibusque ad ipsam medietatem de predicta corte, tam in terris quam in
                        aquis pertinere videntur; reliqua vero pars media ipsius cortis ad
                        proprietate ipsum monesterium detinet. Sed et de <rs key="#Castle"
                            >castello</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Castle #Defensive_elements" ref="#places/133"
                            >Casalappi</placeName>, septem <rs key="#Defensive_elements">merli</rs>
                        de predicto castello, cum suis pertinentiis que detinet <persName><name
                                ref="Teudicius">Tedici</name></persName>; et <rs key="#Mountains"
                            >Poio</rs> qui vocatur <placeName>Capanna Murata</placeName>, totum in
                        integrum cum suis pertinentiis. Et alia <rs key="#Curtes">corte</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Curtes #Mansi #Churches" ref="#estates/241"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Mansi #Churches" ref="#places/382"
                            >Aslaito</placeName></geogName>, cum medietate de <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Mansi #Churches">Sancti Michaelis que vocatur in
                            Nottula</orgName> cum septem <rs key="#Mansi">mase</rs>. Sed et alia <rs
                            key="#Curtes">corte</rs> que nominatur <geogName key="#Curtes #Churches"
                                ><placeName key="#Curtes #Churches">Serignano</placeName></geogName>
                        cum sua pertinentia, et <rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/208">Sancti
                            Andree</orgName> cum sua pertinentia. Unde quero ad vos, donnus
                        cancellarius et missus, ut vos propter Deum et anime domni imperatoris ac
                        vestre mercedis, ut investiatis me et parti predicti monesterii de is
                        omnibus rebus ad salva querela, quoqusque ipsi Bonefacius et Eppo et
                        Rainerius ad vestrum placito veninant, et ad predicti monesterii iustitiam
                        faciant”. Cum ipse Lanfrancus avocatus taliter retulisent, tunc domnus
                        Gunterius cancelarius et missus per fuste, quam sua tenebat manum,
                        investivit predictum Lanfrancum avocatum et predictum monesterium de
                        suprascriptis medietatibus vel duabus curtibus, siccuti supra denominantur
                        ad salva querellam, quodusque predictus Bonefacius et Eppo et Rainerius ad
                        placitum veniant et predicti monesterii iusticia faciant. Et insuper mixit
                            <rs key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">bannum</rs> ex parte domni
                        imperatoris, ut nullus quislibet eundem Lanfrancum parte predicti monesterii
                        de is omnibus rebus devestire molestare vel inquietare audeat sine legale
                        iudicio. Qui vero fecerit centum libras auri se conpoxiturus agnoscad,
                        medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere</rs> domni imperatoris, medietatem
                        parti predicti monesterii. Et ac noticia qualiter acta est causa fieri
                        amonuerunt. Quidem et ego <persName key="#Writer #Notary"><name ref="Aldus"
                                >Aldus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> sacri palaci et iusione suprascripto
                        cancelalarii et misso seu iudicum amonicione scripsi. Hanno ab incarnacione
                        domini nostris Iesu Christi milleximo quimquageximo quinto, imperii vero
                        domni secundi Einrigi Deo propicio nono, quartodecimo die mensis iunii,
                        indicione octava. Ego Guntherius cancellarius confirmavi (SR). (S)
                        Bonusfilius <rs key="#Judge">iudex</rs> sacri palatii interfuit. (S) Atzo
                        iudex et <rs key="#Missus_regis">missus</rs> domni imperatoris interfuit.
                        (S) Ego Otto iudex sacri palatii interfui. (S) Ego Wibertus iudex sacri
                        palacii interfui. (S) Ego Burgundius iudex sacri palatii interfui. (S)
                        Walcausus iudex sacri palatii interfuit.</ab>
                        </div>
